[1. General description of data]{.mark}

[Our research is based on tiff image datasets (immunofluorescence data).
Raw images will be saved in persistent storage.]{.mark}

[When performing the research, raw images will be segmented into small
tiles/patches, stored in project scratch and reused. Deep learning
models will be trained on image tiles and checkpoints are also saved in
project scratch. Models to be kept will be moved to persistent
storage.]{.mark}

[Scripts will be saved in user home and use GitHub for version
control.]{.mark}

[The total size of the raw image will be approximately 500GB.]{.mark}

[The size of segmented patches will be \~500GB.]{.mark}

[2. Opening, publishing and archiving the data after the research
project]{.mark}

[After the termination of the project, data could be kept in LUMI for 30
days and then deleted. The tiff image dataset is our in-house dataset
but has already been published. All the scripts and results will be
available on GitHub and Synapse for manuscript publication. The data
will be transferred to our lab storage and the downstream analysis and
visualization will be performed on lab work stations.]{.mark}

